content.description: Sit start the far left arête.
content.location: This ascends the far left arête.

content.description: Sit start roughly in the center of the face with left hand on a decent knob and right hand on a small crimp and move straight up to a distant right hand triangular pinch and a small left hand dish and top out. Problem avoids the somewhat detached block.
content.location: This ascends the steep face a few feet left of the tree stump.

content.description: Sit start a few feet right of the left arête with your left hand on a faint sidepull sloper and your right hand on the decent knob. Fire right hand to the triangular pinch, then move left hand to a dish, climb up, and top out. This problem avoids the somewhat detached block.
content.location: This problem is located between the problems Whiskey and Tuning Fork.

content.description: Sit start matched on a thin crimp bar with the tree stump between your legs. Move up to crimps, then move left and match on the triangular pinch, power left to the dish, and top out. The problem doesn't make use of the somewhat detached block.
content.location: Start roughly where the tree stump is on the right side of the face about 4-5 feet right of the problem Tuning Fork.

content.description: White Boulder is one lone, decent block that is a whitish-gray color and sits on the shore. All the problems currently listed on this boulder are located on the steeper side that has a small one foot tree stump.
